the ""mudhad"" or ""madhad"" or madadh are warrior tribe of suryavanshi rajputs, still can be found in karnal, panipat, jind, kurukshetra, gurgaon, kaithal, haryana and punjab. some famous villages of madadh rajputs in haryana are rajound, salwan, ghauranda, batta, kalayat, rahara, singhana (sarpdaman) muana etc. a few mudhad are also found in saharanpur district in uttar pradesh. in district gujrat, tehsil kharian village named madhad, madadh are considered (raghav) and generally used surname rana.